and 55% across neuroimaging modalities. This pattern\nremains virtually unchanged when considering only acutely or chronically\ndepressed patients. Differences are comparable to those found for PRS, but\nsubstantially smaller than for environmental variables. Discussion: We provide\na large-scale, multimodal analysis of univariate biological differences between\nMDD patients and controls and show that even under near-ideal conditions and\nfor maximum biological differences, deviations are extremely small and\nsimilarity dominates. We sketch an agenda for a new focus of future research in\nbiological psychiatry facilitating quantitative, theory-driven research, an\nemphasis on computational psychiatry and multivariate machine learning\napproaches, as well as the utilization of ecologically valid phenotyping.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Dec 2021 18:27:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-21"}
