on to the heat capacity an approach\nbased on a reasonable frequency spectrum is adopted. Taking advantage of the\nin-field heat capacity measurements MCE was described in terms of the\nisothermal entropy change $\\Delta S_\\mathrm{M}$ and the adiabatic temperature\nchange $\\Delta T_\\mathrm{ad}$. The magnitudes of these quantities are typical\nfor the class of molecular magnets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Dec 2021 18:30:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-21"}
