 in triples, where in the majority the tertiary black\nhole is able to perturb their long-term evolution. Our results show that triple\ninteractions are key to a full understanding of massive star evolution and\ncompact object binary formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Dec 2021 19:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 9 Oct 2022 20:32:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-11"}
