ow effective dimensionality\nin the model. We show how information geometry can motivate new, natural\nparameterizations that improve the stability and interpretation of uncertainty\nquantification analysis and further suggest simplified, less-sloppy models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Dec 2021 20:45:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 May 2022 15:19:45 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 13 May 2022 17:15:17 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 15 Jun 2022 01:55:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-16"}
